<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-07-19T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-07-19T16:00:00-05:00" n="271" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d271">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/6019: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-19T22:00:00+01:00">July 19, 1937—10
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received July 19—8:42 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1010. With regard to Spain, Delbos remarked to me this evening that he
                            did not believe there was any chance of the British proposal being
                            accepted. It would, however, serve to delay a crisis.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>